Rodney Todd and his seven children aged six to 15 died from carbon monoxide poisoning in their Princess Anne home on April 6 . 
  The Todd family - a 36-year-old father and his children - were poisoned in their sleep only days after the power company discovered a stolen meter . 
  Father Rodney Todd was raising the children after divorcing their mother in November . 
  The six-hour funeral service brought 1,200 people to the Ella Fitzgerald Auditorium at the University of Maryland Eastern Shore on Saturday . 
  The family was poisoned as they slept in their home . 
  The children have been named as boys Cameron Todd, 13, and Zycheim Todd, 7; and girls Tynijuiza Todd, 15